 *  - The Primary Chronicle / Apostle Andrew passage is framed as the earliest
 *    *written/literary* description, not verified history (the chronicle
 *    contains embellished legends).
 *  - Etymology given per scholarly consensus: Greek balaneîon → Latin
 *    balneum → Proto-Slavic → баня. The romanticised "makes pain go away"
 *    folk etymology is NOT repeated.
 *  - Bannik and venik benefits described as traditional belief, not science.
